    <article id="html"> <h2> HTML Learning Section</h2>
        <section>
            <h3>Things I have learned about HTML so far. </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language</li>
                    <li>HTML is used to create web pages</li>
                    <li>HTML uses tags to structure content</li>
                    <li>Common HTML tags include &lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;, &lt;p&gt;, &lt;a&gt;, &lt;img&gt;, &lt;ul&gt;, &lt;ol&gt;, and &lt;li&gt;</li>
                    <li>Attributes provide additional information about HTML elements</li>
                    <li>HTML5 is the latest version of HTML</li>
                </ul>
            <h3>My daily schedule for learning HTML. </h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Wake up early</li>
                <li>Have breakfast</li>
                <li>Study HTML and CSS</li>
                <li>Practice coding</li>
                <li>Work on projects</li>
                <li>Relax and unwind</li>   
            </ol>
